        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): unwrap standalone message tool JSON",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Unwrap standalone downgraded `message` tool JSON during final assistant `message_end` delivery.\n- Preserve the existing diagnostic warning path and add a focused regression for the `openai-completions`-style leaked envelope.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-subscribe.handlers.messages.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Standalone assistant text shaped like `{\"name\":\"message\",\"arguments\":{\"action\":\"send\",\"message\":\"...\"}}` no longer posts that JSON envelope during message_end delivery; OpenClaw delivers the `message` argument text instead.\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw test checkout in the dedicated worktree.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-subscribe.handlers.messages.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\nEvidence after fix: The new `handleMessageEnd` regression delivered the extracted message text through `emitBlockReply` and the focused Vitest file passed.\nObserved result after fix: 29 tests passed, including the regression for the `openai-completions`-style message-tool JSON envelope.\nWhat was not tested: Live Discord/openai-completions end-to-end delivery; streamed `text_delta` or chunked delivery variants are intentionally outside this small patch.\n",
